Text: I love Romani. They are wonderful people who are fun, hospitable, ingenious, and have a fascinating culture. One of my closest friends is 1/4 Roma and her family is a real bunch of characters! They also obnoxiously will attempt to buy any jewelry or electronics off of you ("Nice camera! I buy? I buy? How much? How much?"). So, unfortunately, the stereotype of Romani being thieves has some truth to it. But can you blame them? It's like an earlier poster said: it's kinda a vicious cycle.
